00:47:32.929 --> 00:47:35.098
you think deciding to work
makes a job appear?

00:47:35.098 --> 00:47:36.366
Good grief.

00:47:36.366 --> 00:47:37.934
- Seriously?
- And to be blunt,

00:47:37.934 --> 00:47:39.469
even if we move,

00:47:39.469 --> 00:47:41.405
you can find some job you can do there.

00:47:41.405 --> 00:47:43.774
why be picky about doing
what you want at your age?

00:47:43.774 --> 00:47:44.541
Am I wrong?

00:47:45.809 --> 00:47:48.545
Anyway, don't take it too hard.

00:47:48.545 --> 00:47:50.080
We'll talk when I'm back. Bye.

00:47:51.348 --> 00:47:53.150
Right, and the braised tofu was good.

00:47:55.686 --> 00:47:58.455
What's wrong with my age?

00:48:12.636 --> 00:48:13.470
Hello?

00:48:13.470 --> 00:48:14.838
Ms. Cho, where are you?

00:48:14.838 --> 00:48:16.974
There's a place for rent
in the complex at a cheap price.

00:48:16.974 --> 00:48:17.874
Really?

00:48:18.241 --> 00:48:20.444
Yes, ma'am. I'm on my way.

00:48:20.444 --> 00:48:23.013
I'm literally running now.
Please wait a bit.

00:48:23.013 --> 00:48:24.481
Yes, we're coming.

00:48:25.382 --> 00:48:27.918
They just came by
but haven't decided yet.

00:48:27.918 --> 00:48:29.219
Thank goodness.

00:48:29.219 --> 00:48:31.421
The owner has three homes.

00:48:31.421 --> 00:48:33.423
No loans, very clean.

00:48:33.957 --> 00:48:36.026
The previous tenant
suddenly had to go abroad,

00:48:36.026 --> 00:48:38.562
and will leave furniture
and appliances if needed.

00:48:38.562 --> 00:48:40.330
- Jackpot.
- Total jackpot.

00:48:40.330 --> 00:48:41.932
- Hurry, let's go check it out.
- Yes.

00:48:42.466 --> 00:48:45.168
I'm happy for you.
We have to hurry.

00:48:45.168 --> 00:48:46.970
Please wait.

00:48:47.671 --> 00:48:48.705
Thank you.

00:48:54.044 --> 00:48:55.312
What floor was it?

00:48:55.679 --> 00:48:56.847
Eleventh.

00:49:08.125 --> 00:49:10.093
Text the owner...

00:49:10.093 --> 00:49:11.895
that I'll wire the holding deposit
in ten minutes.

00:49:12.562 --> 00:49:14.531
When the door opens, run straight ahead.

00:49:14.531 --> 00:49:15.565
It's unit 1106.

00:49:15.565 --> 00:49:18.068
But they got on the elevator first.

00:49:18.368 --> 00:49:19.603
I feel bad about it.

00:49:21.038 --> 00:49:24.474
Our Father forgives the houseless.

00:49:24.474 --> 00:49:25.309
Good luck.

00:49:46.964 --> 00:49:49.266
- We got here first.
- It's not that way.

00:49:49.266 --> 00:49:51.268
It's not there. Come.

00:49:51.268 --> 00:49:53.003
It's not that way.
It's this way.

00:49:53.003 --> 00:49:54.471
- Hurry.
- Run.

00:49:56.707 --> 00:49:58.108
Faster.

00:49:58.108 --> 00:50:00.043
It's not there.

00:50:03.146 --> 00:50:04.414
Come on.

00:50:26.436 --> 00:50:27.838
Sorry.

00:50:27.838 --> 00:50:29.139
I pressed it first.

00:50:36.813 --> 00:50:39.016
How are you so fast?

00:50:39.750 --> 00:50:42.085
You must've been athletic back in the day.

00:50:43.086 --> 00:50:45.889
I really hate losing, that's all.

00:50:45.889 --> 00:50:47.291
Me too.

00:50:47.291 --> 00:50:49.726
When I saw that lady earlier...

00:50:49.960 --> 00:50:52.062
She's here.

00:50:53.263 --> 00:50:54.798
Say hello.
She's the owner of the house.

00:50:54.798 --> 00:50:55.932
Hello.

00:50:55.932 --> 00:50:57.734
- Ma'am, could I get a glass of water?
- Sure.

00:50:59.569 --> 00:51:01.672
Once I said I'd sign with you,

00:51:01.672 --> 00:51:04.341
every real estate office
kept calling nonstop.

00:51:04.875 --> 00:51:07.577
It makes me think
I should switch to monthly next time.

00:51:07.577 --> 00:51:10.747
Don't say that.

00:51:10.747 --> 00:51:13.083
You'll scare the tenant.

00:51:14.351 --> 00:51:15.652
Cheer up.

00:51:15.652 --> 00:51:19.256
She doesn't change her mind easily.

00:51:30.801 --> 00:51:31.702
Jjon Na Jeong?

00:51:35.872 --> 00:51:39.209
You used to live in Hanmae-dong.

00:51:39.476 --> 00:51:40.877
You're Cho Na Jeong, aren't you?

00:51:41.912 --> 00:51:43.113
Yes.

00:51:44.581 --> 00:51:46.783
It's me, Mi Sook.

00:51:47.417 --> 00:51:49.152
Yang Mi Sook.

00:51:54.691 --> 00:51:56.159
(Cho Na Jeong)

00:51:56.159 --> 00:51:58.061
Yang Mi Sook, anywhere you want to go?

00:51:58.061 --> 00:51:59.396
How about a karaoke?

00:52:00.030 --> 00:52:02.332
There's a karaoke right up front.
Should we go there?

00:52:02.332 --> 00:52:03.233
Hey.

00:52:03.934 --> 00:52:05.135
Why are you ignoring me?

00:52:05.802 --> 00:52:07.704
I didn't see you, so what?

00:52:08.505 --> 00:52:09.640
Bullshit.

00:52:10.874 --> 00:52:11.742
Who's that?

00:52:12.409 --> 00:52:14.778
Her? The class president.

00:52:15.579 --> 00:52:17.848
She grinds alone to succeed
and studies like a maniac.

00:52:17.848 --> 00:52:18.849
She's ruthless.

00:52:19.916 --> 00:52:21.685
But she's kind of cute.

00:52:22.352 --> 00:52:24.655
You crazy bastard,
are you out of your mind?

00:52:24.655 --> 00:52:26.390
Fine. Just find someone
so we can pair off.

00:52:27.224 --> 00:52:28.292
Hey, Jjon Na Jeong.

00:52:28.725 --> 00:52:31.161
Since we're unpaired right now,

00:52:31.428 --> 00:52:33.664
how about hitting a karaoke
for just two hours?

00:52:36.266 --> 00:52:37.067
And of course,

00:52:37.801 --> 00:52:38.935
you're paying.

00:52:40.304 --> 00:52:43.206
Does your mom know
this is what you're doing?

00:52:43.206 --> 00:52:44.341
What?

00:52:44.341 --> 00:52:47.010
I was in the teachers' office last time,

00:52:47.010 --> 00:52:49.246
and your mom was bawling
in front of our homeroom teacher.

00:52:49.846 --> 00:52:53.016
Yang Mi Sook, we're almost in high school.

00:52:53.016 --> 00:52:55.052
How long are you going to keep
wasting time like this?

00:52:55.052 --> 00:52:56.253
What are you going to do with your life?

00:52:56.253 --> 00:52:58.488
You crazy bitch.
Who are you to lecture me?

00:52:58.488 --> 00:52:59.356
Let go.

00:52:59.356 --> 00:53:01.358
- Let go!
- Stop it.

00:53:01.358 --> 00:53:02.626
You let go first.

00:53:02.626 --> 00:53:03.860
- You first.
- I said let go.

00:53:03.860 --> 00:53:05.162
Stop it.

00:53:05.162 --> 00:53:07.297
- I said let go.
- You first.

00:53:09.399 --> 00:53:12.736
Small world, right, Na Jeong?

00:53:12.736 --> 00:53:14.838
Yes, tell me about it.

00:53:15.505 --> 00:53:17.107
How have you been all this time?

00:53:17.107 --> 00:53:19.810
I think I vaguely heard
you went to Yeonhee University.

00:53:19.810 --> 00:53:20.978
I did.

00:53:21.845 --> 00:53:23.013
Are you married?

00:53:23.547 --> 00:53:24.281
Yes.

00:53:24.281 --> 00:53:25.248
Kids?

00:53:25.515 --> 00:53:26.383
Two.

00:53:26.717 --> 00:53:27.951
Daughters? Sons?

00:53:28.251 --> 00:53:29.386
Two sons.

00:53:32.356 --> 00:53:33.523
Are they well-behaved?

00:53:34.157 --> 00:53:36.393
Boys tend to be rough on the house.

00:53:37.294 --> 00:53:40.397
No. My kids are super calm.

00:53:40.397 --> 00:53:43.066
The downstairs neighbor even asked
if we had kids at all.

00:53:43.066 --> 00:53:44.801
"I thought you didn't have any kids."

00:53:44.801 --> 00:53:46.603
They were shocked and even said this.

00:53:54.044 --> 00:53:54.878
Hey.

00:53:55.112 --> 00:53:57.381
What kind of business did you do...

00:53:57.381 --> 00:53:58.982
to get that rich?

00:53:58.982 --> 00:54:01.418
I heard from the real estate agent
that you own three houses.

00:54:01.418 --> 00:54:02.619
That's amazing.

00:54:04.321 --> 00:54:07.357
I quit school in senior year...

00:54:07.357 --> 00:54:08.825
and went to Australia to study.

00:54:09.026 --> 00:54:12.095
When I came back to Korea,
I started working in Dongdaemun.

00:54:12.095 --> 00:54:15.198
When the live-commerce era began,
it was like I'd found my wave.

00:54:15.198 --> 00:54:16.667
I started selling clothes
through live streams,

00:54:16.667 --> 00:54:19.303
expanded the business, and that took off.

00:54:19.770 --> 00:54:20.637
Hey.

00:54:20.837 --> 00:54:22.039
Hey.

00:54:25.108 --> 00:54:27.144
Do you know what they call this?

00:54:29.012 --> 00:54:31.214
Ladies, no other shop has this.

00:54:31.214 --> 00:54:33.750
Look. If you order right now, I'll...

00:54:33.750 --> 00:54:35.986
A mobile show host.

00:54:37.854 --> 00:54:40.257
They say life's full of downs and ups.

00:54:42.125 --> 00:54:44.161
But you know, I always had that in me.

00:54:44.761 --> 00:54:47.931
The pioneering spirit
to take paths others wouldn't.

00:54:47.931 --> 00:54:49.967
The nerve and confidence...

00:54:49.967 --> 00:54:53.003
to say "no" when others said "yes."

00:54:56.873 --> 00:54:57.874
What about you?

00:54:58.175 --> 00:54:59.810
Aren't you working?

00:55:00.544 --> 00:55:01.411
No.

00:55:02.212 --> 00:55:03.380
Right.

00:55:03.380 --> 00:55:05.649
At our age, working's not easy.

00:55:06.383 --> 00:55:08.485
That's true.

00:55:08.485 --> 00:55:09.486
My gosh.

00:55:09.486 --> 00:55:11.622
Weren't you on JBN News recently?

00:55:11.622 --> 00:55:13.657
Some fair for women
with career breaks or something.

00:55:17.160 --> 00:55:19.196
You saw it.

00:55:19.196 --> 00:55:20.364
Hey.

00:55:20.631 --> 00:55:23.200
I thought, "Isn't that Cho Na Jeong?"
but wasn't sure.

00:55:23.200 --> 00:55:24.267
But it was you.

00:55:24.267 --> 00:55:26.236
The woman who said
she wanted to work again.

00:55:31.608 --> 00:55:32.676
How'd she see that?

00:55:33.543 --> 00:55:35.479
Hey, perfect timing.

00:55:35.479 --> 00:55:37.247
You said you're looking for a job, right?

00:55:37.247 --> 00:55:38.382
I actually need someone.

00:55:38.382 --> 00:55:39.916
No, it's fine, Mi Sook.

00:55:40.884 --> 00:55:42.052
Fine? What's fine?

00:55:43.620 --> 00:55:45.188
Didn't you say you're job-hunting?

00:55:45.188 --> 00:55:47.424
Does it hurt your pride to work under me?

00:55:50.360 --> 00:55:52.329
You still have that way
of getting under people's skin.

00:55:53.130 --> 00:55:56.733
Hey, you won't get anywhere
if you keep being so complacent.

00:55:56.733 --> 00:55:58.135
No matter how successful you were before,

00:55:58.135 --> 00:56:01.004
you're just a housewife
rotting away at home now.

00:56:01.605 --> 00:56:03.807
Honestly, women who only
raise kids at home...

00:56:03.807 --> 00:56:05.542
don't even get chances like this.

00:56:07.077 --> 00:56:09.746
This is why it's so hard
to talk to stay-at-home moms.

00:56:09.746 --> 00:56:12.616
No, it's not that, Mi Sook.

00:56:13.250 --> 00:56:16.186
I already got another offer
to work with someone else,

00:56:16.186 --> 00:56:17.688
that's why I can't.

00:56:17.688 --> 00:56:19.423
Don't get me wrong.

00:56:21.491 --> 00:56:25.095
I wasn't going to say this
because I didn't want to sound braggy.

00:56:25.095 --> 00:56:27.731
It would be ridiculous to say this myself.

00:56:28.265 --> 00:56:31.168
But I used to be a show host too,
who pulled in 4,000 a minute.

00:56:31.168 --> 00:56:33.770
So when my face popped up on TV,

00:56:33.770 --> 00:56:37.207
my phone started blowing up
with calls from everywhere.

00:56:37.207 --> 00:56:40.310
So I took a job offer.

00:56:43.246 --> 00:56:44.047
Really?

00:56:46.016 --> 00:56:46.850
From where?

00:56:47.985 --> 00:56:49.186
Sweet Home Shopping.

00:56:51.788 --> 00:56:53.256
Sweet Home Shopping?

00:57:07.004 --> 00:57:08.105
(2005
Na Jeong's Birthday 1)

00:57:08.105 --> 00:57:11.375
I decided I wouldn't live
like the other ladies.

00:57:12.809 --> 00:57:14.778
Even when I grow up,

00:57:15.679 --> 00:57:17.848
I'll never live like other wives.

00:57:18.682 --> 00:57:19.449
Because...

00:57:20.150 --> 00:57:21.752
I was born fabulous.

00:57:23.353 --> 00:57:24.488
I'm young,

00:57:25.222 --> 00:57:26.056
I'm strong,

00:57:27.024 --> 00:57:28.959
and I'm living in the middle
of a grand adventure.

00:57:30.661 --> 00:57:33.363
You can't live complaining all day.

00:57:33.997 --> 00:57:34.865
Wait.

00:57:37.534 --> 00:57:38.535
Naraeng.

00:57:38.802 --> 00:57:39.536
Yes?

00:57:40.170 --> 00:57:41.338
I think...

00:57:41.905 --> 00:57:44.107
maybe you should try again next time.

00:57:46.176 --> 00:57:48.345
What do you mean, Director?

00:57:48.345 --> 00:57:50.314
If you go onstage like this now,

00:57:50.314 --> 00:57:52.649
the other actors will chew us out alive.

00:57:52.649 --> 00:57:54.551
I wasn't good enough.
Please give me another chance.

00:57:54.551 --> 00:57:55.719
I can really pull this off.

00:57:55.719 --> 00:57:58.355
How can you just fire me
without even a warning?

00:57:58.355 --> 00:57:59.690
Everyone, come out now.

00:57:59.690 --> 00:58:04.594
- I have to do this, please.
- Happy birthday to you

00:58:05.295 --> 00:58:09.232
Happy birthday to you

00:58:09.232 --> 00:58:13.737
Happy birthday, dear Cho Naraeng

00:58:13.737 --> 00:58:17.007
Happy birthday to you

00:58:23.013 --> 00:58:24.448
Blow out the candles first.

00:58:24.448 --> 00:58:25.882
One, two, three.

00:58:31.622 --> 00:58:32.823
The final event.

00:59:37.854 --> 00:59:39.790
(Don't call me ma'am)

00:59:40.023 --> 00:59:41.625
